<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1970-09-10T10:10:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1970-09-10T10:10:00-05:00" n="219" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d219">
                        <head>219. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Department of State</gloss>
                            to the <gloss type="to">Embassy in Jordan</gloss><note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d219fn1">Source: National Archives, <gloss target="#t_RG1">RG</gloss> 59, Central Files 1970–73, AV 12.
                                Secret; Immediate; <gloss target="#t_Nodis1">Nodis</gloss>. Drafted
                                by <persName corresp="#p_DRP1">Davies</persName>; cleared by
                                    <persName corresp="#p_JUA1">U. Alexis Johnson</persName> and
                                Curran (S/S); and approved by <persName corresp="#p_SJJ1">Sisco</persName>.</note>
                        </head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1970-09-10T15:10:00+00:00">September 10, 1970,
                                    1510Z</date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>147976. Ref.: State 147736; Amman 4521.<note n="2" xml:id="d219fn2">Telegram 147736 to Amman, September 10, 0032Z. (Ibid.) Telegram
                                4521 is <ref target="#d217">Document 217</ref>.</note> Subject:
                            Hijacking.</p>
                        <list>
                            <label>1.</label>
                            <item>You should proceed to suggest to King Hussein that he pass warning
                                to <gloss target="#t_PFLP1">PFLP</gloss> of direst of consequences
                                if any of hostages should be harmed.</item>
                            <pb facs="0672" n="639" xml:id="pg_639"/>
                            <label>2.</label>
                            <item>Unanimous decision of UNSC September 9 and expressions of outrage
                                not only in West but also in East Bloc can be cited as indication of
                                harm done overall Arab image by current detention hundreds of
                                innocent travellers. Any harm to these could only heighten this
                                feeling to detriment of overall Arab position.</item>
                        </list>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_RWP1">
                                    <hi rend="strong">Rogers</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>